Title: 2006 Saturn VUE sport utility 4 door! V6! Original owner.
Description: I have a beautiful 2006 Saturn VUE for sale. Original owner purchased off the lot in June 2006. 101k miles! It's has the V6. Automatic transmission shifts spotlessly. Title: Toyota Corolla Manual CE 2002 Excellent Condition  110,500 miles
Description: Works great, safe car, easy to driveTwo owners only -- I bought the car at 15,000 miles because the first owner developed dementia soon after purchasing it.  I have all repair and maintenance records.  No accidents except for a couple very minor fendor bendors.  The rear bumper was replaced once, the front just needed cosmetic repair. Manual everything -- doors, windows etc. (except power steering)The only thing it needs is an extra quart of oil between oil changes (age, the mechanic says).  Also the CD player/radio isn't working well.  A/C works great and the mechanic said it's in great condition.There is a very slight dent in the driver's side rear door, but is just cosmetic.  I've kept the paint in great condition with frequent washes and waxes, just has a few dings and minimal rust.I just spent $625 putting on brand new front and rear brakes, pads, rotors and ball joints.  Plan to sell by June 30 so please reply quickly if interested!

Title: 2015 Chevrolet CRUZE great on gas fun to drive EASY to afford - Red
2005 Mitsubishi Lancer Evolution 8
Description: What's going on everyone,Deciding on finally putting up one of my favorite cars ever for sale. Starting a new job and I can't take this 50 miles every single day. This car has been great to me, it is beautiful and a very great car. It is tastefully modified and in overall good shape. Here's the list:(Please read the entire ad before you contact me, just so that you know everything about the car. Please text me if you are interested.)2005 Lancer Evolution GSRCar has a little over 142K miles, CLEAN TITLE in hand! The miles will slightly go up since it is currently my daily.-Tuned by Yusuf from FlyinEVO. (Currently on a conservative tune, at 24 PSI. Car has a manual boost controller. Had the tune looked over and tweaked by Yusuf and he checked it out and confirmed that the car is in great mechanical shape. My dad is a mechanic and I've also had him keep up with the maintenance. The oil was changed every 3k miles, and the car got appropriate tune ups when it was time. The car has been maintained very well. And when you own an Evo, that's crucial..)-VRSF 3.5" intercooler-Function and Form Coilovers-Energy Suspension  bushings on front lower control arms, rear control arms, rear diff, sway bars-New Radiator last spring-Timing belt/balance shaft belt, idler puller and oil filter housing gasket all replaced at 120k-Custom Coil-On-Plug with OEM Honda Coils-Custom LICP-Custom Turboback exhaust with magna flow muffler-Evo X BOV-Perrin Silicone Intake-Innovate Wideband-Prosport Digital Boost Gauge (needs new sender)-Walbro 255-Exedy Stage 1 (replaced at 110k)-All drivetrain fluid replaced last year -New Pads and Rotors (calipers are faded but none are stuck or "bad"-Whiteline RCA Kit-Car just got a brand new WAVETRAC front diff and I have all the paperwork for it, as its still breaking in.Exterior:-Blacked out headlight housings-FXR Retrofit (Morimoto 4300k bulbs with morimoto ballasts)-Powdercoated OEM enkeis-Authentic JDM Rear Bumper-Underbody looks solid for a 13 year old car.Interior:-Seats are in fantastic shape. No major signs of wear at all.-Dual Din conversion with Pioneer bluetooth set upBads:-Car cosmetically isn't in the greatest shape. It isn't bad by any means, but the front bumper could use some work. There are almost no dents or dings anywhere on the car. Driver side side skirt has a scuff near the front tire, and the front bumper has some of the clear coat fading. Windshield has a slight crack in it and would need to be replaced. Other than that, the body looks pretty good for the age.-Car sometimes grinds ever so slightly going into 5th gear. It only happens if you shift quickly. If you shift slowly it won't grind at all. This is a common problem among most Evo 8's. I have seen many of them with this issue, and it was grinding ever since I've owned it. It hasn't gotten worse, but that is why the price is somewhat low, to reflect the cost for repairs if you ever decide to repair it.All in all the car is solid with TONS of potential and runs really well. The car is priced to sell. It is difficult to find an Evo 8 in this type of condition with the given miles. There are no major mods to the engine so it can be a great platform to whoever purchases it. There are many Evo's out there with more than 150K miles, with the grinding issue as well, and the seller is asking $13,500+. I have priced it accordingly and have very little wiggle room on price. I have a clean title in hand and will accept CASH ONLY! Unless you have a check and we go to my bank together and deposit into my account. Please text me as it's the best way to contact me.  . Thank you.

Title: 1995 Camaro
Description: Selling my 1995 Camaro with 140k miles. It is in pretty good condition with normal amounts of wear. NO RUST! Cons:-Driver side window does not work, but I believe it is just the switch in the door. -Small oil leak, which is common for these cars. Requires you to check oil every 4-6 weeks to make sure it is at proper level. -A\C was deleted as I had no need for it.-wear on driver's seat-crack in the upper part of dash from sun.Pros:-T-Tops and the seals are in good condition.-Starts and runs Excellent. My mother drives it occasionally to work.-No body rust which is not typical of these cars.-Other than edge of drivers seat, the interior is very good.-Bose Stereo with oem SubwooferThis is a very solid car that runs and drives well. It is 23 years old though, so it will not be perfect. Selling for 1900 or open to sensible offers.  If interested please call/text  . No trades.

Title: 2010 Nissan Altima HYBRID 81k miles gets 35mpg Very Good Condition!
Description: PERFECT GAS SAVER FOR YOUR COMMUTE, OR FOR RIDESHARING UBER / LYFT!!I'm in no rush to sell and I don't need any help selling the car.Price is FIRM: if I don't get $6,499 I will continue to drive the car until it hits 200-300k miles which I am 100% confident it will reach based on my detailed maintenance.The 2010 Nissan Altima Hybrid was only sold in 8 states.  I purchased this one brand new in 2010 and had it shipped from a dealer in Connecticut.  MSRP: $27,585.  Now it can be yours for less 30% of that!  This car runs PERFECTLY and it's NEVER given me even a single problem.ALL regular and preventative maintenance has been religiously performed at a highly respected Nissan Dealership: Woodfield Nissan in Hoffman Estates.And I have a binder with EVERY receipt from the dealer backing up every service performed.If you're unfamiliar with hybrids, it's very easy: you gas up the car just like a regular car.  When driving, the car will typically run on battery 70-80% of the time (up to 40mph) while the battery is charged.Past 40mph, and to re-charge the battery, the engine kicks in.The range on the car is AMAZING!  The gas tank is 20 gallons and the car typically achieves 550-600 miles on a single tank!  Do you know how great it is only having to fill up gas every 3-4 weeks?  In the winter you will achieve 475-500 miles on the tank, in the summer 575-650!I will do my best to describe the car.  It has most all the options you would want: Alloy wheels, power windows/doors, dual zone digital climate control, cruise control, AM/FM/CD with aux input for your phone or media device.  It has very clean cloth seats.The Good:1. Mechanically perfect, runs and drives like a dream.2. LOW miles. 3. Well optioned.4. No rust!5. 35mpg City and 33mpg highway.  I have a spreadsheet with details on every single fillup and the mpg achieved.  Over 142 tanks the car has averaged 32.89mpg combined city/highway driving.  It's the PERFECT commuter car.  My commute was 18 miles one-way in mixed bumper-to-bumper and freeway driving and the car shines in both!  The most miles I've achieved on a single tank is 693 (in the mild spring/summer) and the worst is 441 (in the freezing winter)6. Rarely parked on the mean Chicago streets; I almost always had a private spot or garage spot.The Less Good:1. Some minor body damage.  Car was recently hit while parked and has minor damage to the driver side quarter panel (and no, they didn't leave a note!), but this is cosmetic only, the car still runs like new!2) It's been in 2 minor accidents: a) I was stopped at a red light and the car behind me got rear ended and pushed into me, scratches to bumper repaired by their insurance. b) I literally got hit by a Mac truck that started hydroplaning and lost control on I90, damaged my driver side quarter panel, replaced by dealer through their insuranceLowball offers will be ignored so save yourself the time.  Thanks for looking!

Title: 1991 MITSUBISHI DELICA STAR WAGON RARE JAPANESE IMPORT
Description: You have now just discovered a Very Rarely seen and Extremely Interesting 1991 Mitsubishi Delica Star Wagon. For those of you who are not fully aware of this model which most people aren't, let's give you a reader's digest update on this Japanese Import. Initial the Mitsubishi Delica was built by Mitsubishi for the Japanese market and then branched distribution out to Australia, New Zealand and other Asian Countries and offered in a few different configurations. This particular L300 Star wagon was produced primarily as a transporter for humans. It has seating for up to 8 passengers, is a Right-Hand Drive and Is powered by a 2.5 Liter Turbo Diesel Engine and linked to a 5-Speed Manual Transmission and offers 4-Wheel Drive with both High and Low Range. This Drivetrain is the most preferred combination that was available as they did produce gas versions with automatic transmission with just front wheel drive. These Star wagons are now just hitting the North American Market as in order to import here they must be at least 25 years old to do so. These Mitsubishi Star Wagons a lot of versatility for the right individual from transporting passengers, extreme off roading and Ideal for the outdoorsman who heads out in the heavy bush for hunting and fishing. They also have been sighted by delivery companies who can pull out all the rear seats and have the luxury of the economy and reliability of a Turbo Diesel and the option of 4-Wheel Drive to get you thru those record snow days. The uses are almost endless. If you somewhat skeptical of this Star Wagons off Road capabilities there are several you tube videos showing just how rugged and agile these Star Wagons are. VEHICLE FEATURES AND HIGHLIGHTS:1991 MITSUBISHI L300 STAR WAGON 4X4JAPANESE IMPORT (STREET LEGAL AND TITLED)RIGHT HAND DRIVE2.5 LITER TURBO DIESEL5-SPEED MANUAL WITH 2-SPEED 4-WHEEL TRANSFER CASESEATING FOR UP TO 8 PASSENGERSVERSITLE ADJUTABLE REAR SEATS WITH FLIP FLOP 1ST ROW BENCHFRONT BRUSH GUARDLEFT SIDE SLIDING DOOR WITH STEP UPTITNTED GLASS WITH A/CLARGE FUSO STYLED MIRRORS BOTH FRONT AND BACK2-TONE PAINT (CORAL BLUE OVER SOFIA WHITE)125,514 km OR 77,990 MILESFACTORY AM/FM/CASSETTE WITH CDPlease take a look at the many photos of this very interesting 1991 Mitsubishi L300 Star Wagon and form your own opinion. You will either love it or not. lol. It's not for everyone but if you're looking for something very different that you don't see everyday and are looking for more than just a plain mini van that can get you off road and is very economic, your ship has come in. This right-hand drive L300 is very easy and fun to drive and gets many double takes and tons of thumbs up where ever you're driving it.TRANSIT MERCEDES CARGO VAN TRANSPORTER CARAVAN VW BUS SPRINTER

Title: 2001 Chevy tahoe
Description: I have a 2001 Chevy tahoe for sale. Has the 5.7 v8. 180000m miles on it. Has some rust where most of these vehicles get it. You can see in the pics. Has a dent by the front passenger side headlight. Has a small dent rear passenger side by bumper. Leather interior front seats have the normal cracks but no major chunks missing. Heated seats work power everything. The passenger window regulator went out so I have the window propped up right now. I just ordered the new part will include if I don't have it replaced before someone wants it. 4x4 works. It starts,runs and drives as it should. It's currently my daily driver and has been since I bought it 4 years ago. Tires are about 50%. It's a good truck. It's like sitting on a throne driving it but I'm looking for something a little newer now and smaller. Let me know if you're interested.

Title: 2015 CHEVY CRUZE EXCELLENT CONDITION 54,000 MILES MANUAL TRANSMISSION
Description: Excellent condition 2015 Chevy Cruze with MANUAL TRANSMISSION and 54,000 miles.  Very clean well cared for car that gets about 38 all around, real world miles per gallon.  This car has a rebuilt title from a minor front end impact with a deer that was professionally repaired.  There is a dent in the passenger side rocker that can be seen in photos.  Fantastic all around economical car that gets crazy good gas mileage.

Title: 1955 Chevy 210 Handyman (Sell or trade)
Description: Perfect black paint on amazingly laser straight sheet metal,A custom black and grey leather and suede interior by Premier Upholstery,A big block 396 engine with a TH400 transmission,This absolutely rust-free car was purchased in Arizona. It even retains its original rust-free floor pan and floor pan braces. Again, there is absolutely no rust on this '55 Handyman. Have pictures showing wagon stripped during build.After the car was purchased in Arizona, the interior was removed to allow the body shop to really get in and make this car straight with awesome gaps. Bruce Tschida and his team at Lake Marion Collision (Lakeville MN) removed the glass, the doors, the hood, the tailgate and all of the stainless and chrome in order to really make this black wagon pop. The paint is Sikkens black. This black wagon is laser straight, even the roof.The dash was re-wired with an ATO fuse panel. A Dakota Digital VHX instrument panel was installed with the main control board mounted with Velcro to allow easy access. A stock-appearing AAR radio with AM/FM/iPod/MP3 and Kenwood speakers were installed. A Vintage Air Gen IV heating/cooling system was installed with the outboard vents installed in the dash itself just as they did at the factory. The AC blows cold. A billet aluminum face panel with a quartz stock-appearing clock completes the dash. The doors have power windows with a master controller in the driver's door.The interior was provided by the award-wining shop, Premier Upholstery (Rogers, MN). The custom leather interior is black and grey and is complemented a suede headliner and by loop pile carpet with matching floor mats. Billet Specialties black leather insert steering wheel which is mounted on an Ididit tilt column. The engine started life as a 325 hp 396 big block. It has since been upgraded with a Comp Cam, 454 heads, a Weiand aluminum intake manifold, an Edelbrock carburetor, MSD ignition and a high volume Edelbrock fuel pump. The exhaust is through 3" ceramic coated Doug's headers and Magnaflow mufflers. The engine runs great, doesn't use oil and holds a steady 60 psig oil pressure down the road.Cooling is provided by an aluminum Rod Davis radiator with a flex fan and two (2) electric fans controlled from a Dakota Digital fan controller. The engine does not overheat even on a 90 plus degree day with the AC blasting.The engine compartment has a "one-off" sheet metal cover that covers the twin electric fans, the radiator, the billet radiator overflow tank, the transmission cooler, the A/C condenser, the horn and the billet power steering reservoir. The cover is easily removed with a hex head driver.Also, under the hood, is an Optima gel-cell battery with a billet hold-down bracket. Billet aluminum is also used for the alternator and the accessories brackets (power steering pump, the alternator and the A/C compressor). Chrome round-head hex bolts complete the unique "look" under the hood. To top things off, two lights with switches are mounted in the engine compartment.The suspension consists of a power rack and pinion system from Ecklers and a Hotchkiss front anti-sway bar. The front spindles are dropped Heidt's with lowered springs and KYN shocks. There are power disk brakes in front and drum brakes in the rear powered by an 8" dual diaphragm booster and a CCR dual master. It corners level and stops on a dime.The rear is a narrowed 9" posi Ford with 3:50 gears, and KYN shocks. The stock gas tank is new as is the spare tire well. Both were removed sometime in the past for a custom gas tank. Now there is a spare tire and a jack--just to be on the safe side.The tires are BF Goodrich G-Force Super Sport just installed June 2015. They are mounted on American Racing polished aluminum Torq-Thrust wheels with 17"x7" in front and 17"x8" in the rear.This is as close to a #1 car as you can get and still have it driven on the street. Build has way in excess of $70,000 in it.Car runs cool, even with 90 deg plus day with the air on. Have 2 books with cut sheets for the car and pictures showing restoration.Will consider trade or partial trade and cash.Don't hesitate making a cash offer.

Title: 1955 Ford Crown Victoria
Description: This 1955 Ford Crown Victoria is a striking and gorgeous two-tone example impeccably finished in the desirable combination of Torch Red and white, which continues throughout the interior with excellent vinyl seats. Power comes from the original 292ci Y-block V8 engine paired with a smooth-shifting Ford-O-Matic automatic transmission. The interior features a gorgeous perforated headliner in white, Ford Magic Air ventilation and heat system, dash clock and a push-button AM radio with rotary dial. This Crown Victoria rides on chrome wire wheels wrapped in wide whitewall tires and features an airplane hood ornament, remote spotlight, fender skirts, trunk mat and spare tire. This outstanding example is in fabulous condition throughout and has been in a prestigious collection for many years. Please visit kingcorvettes.com for more photos and a video. Title: 1946  Studebaker Champion Skyway Business Coupe
Description: 1946 STUDEBAKER CHAMPION SKYWAY BUSINESS COUPEYOU HAVE THE OPPORTUNITY TO BUY A VERY RARE CAR ! AFTER WWII ENDED IN 1946 ,STUDEBAKER STARTED PRODUCING CARS AGAIN,BUT ONLY FOR TWO MONTH BEFORE SWITCHING OVER TO THE 1947 MODELS CARS . BECAUSE OF THIS , LESS THAN 2000 COUPES WERE PRODUCED IN 1946 MODELS. THE ANTIQUE STUDEBAKER CLUB CONSIDERS THIS CAR PRE-WAR SINCE ITS A CONTINUATION OF THE 1942 MODELS,WITH A FEW EXCEPTIONS, MOST NOTABLY THE GRILLE.ITS BEEN IN DRYSTORAGE SINCE 2001 THAT I KNOW OF, PROBABLY LONGER. IT HAS A VERY NICE DASHBOARD AND STEERING WHEEL. THE SPLIT-BACK BENCH SEAT ALLOWS ACCESS TO THE TRUNK AREA. THE UPHOLSTERY STILL THE ORIGINAL . THERE ARE CURTAINS ON THE PACKAGE SHELF , WHICH HIDE CONTENTS IN THE TRUNK. IT HAS 60499 ORIGINAL MILES ON THE ODOMETER. 6 CYLINDERS ENGINE WITH A MANUAL 3 SPEED ON THE TREE TRANSMISSION WITH OVER DRIVE ,THE CAR RUNS DRIVE AND STOP VERY WELL .THE EXTERIOR OF THE CAR PAINT IS ORIGINAL DARK BLUE WITH FADE AREAS MOSTLY IN THE HOOD ,SOME RUST UNDER THE REAR ROCK GUARDS,AND THE REAR TRUNK BACK FLOOR SHOWING IN PICTURES .4 NEW FRESH TIRES, NEW 6 V BATTERY, NEW BRAKE MASTER CYLINDER AND WHEEL CYLINDERS, ALL FRONT END BUSHING WERE REPLACED . HEATHER UNDER DRIVER SEAT, FRONT WINDSHIELD NEED REPLACED (PROVIDED). WINDOWS VENTS NEED REPLACEMENT SEE PICTURES IN DETAIL PLEASE ,MISSING DRIVER DOOR PANELS,EXTRA PARTS COMMING WITH THE CAR:NEW WATER PUMP (EXISTING NOISY BUT NOT LEAKING)NEW FRONT WINDSHIELDS IN BOX2 NEW ROCK GUARDS FROM REAR FENDERTHIS IS A REAL TIME CAPSULE AND A GOOD CHANCE TO GET AN AMERICAN LEGEND AND BEAUTIFUL COUPE WITH AN INCREDIBLE MILAGE AND CONDITIONHAS A CLEAN AND CLEAR STATE OF WASHINGTON TITLE"For Coupe Lovers, this one is really cool"BUYER IS RESPONSABLE FOR SHIPPING COSTCAR IS SOLD AS IS WHERE ISTHANK YOU!

Title: 1997 Infiniti Q45 VIP Car
Description: REPOSTING, LAST DEAL FELL THROUGH.$1750VIP car project.Infiniti Q45Highlights-VOLK GTA-V wheels with tiresSpecs: 19x9.5 and 19x10.5 +17 and +22-Legit JDM Junction Produce accessories inside-S14 adjustable coilovers in the rear-stock motor Cons:-car has been sitting for over a year due to the electrical harness getting chewed up by the front driver  wheel, in the wheel well. Poor factory location, common issue on slammed Nissans/Infiniti.-i have a replacement harness to extend and correct this issue that I will include-bad dead battery-all old fluids, plugs, wires. I doubt the car will start with a fresh battery so I suggest a tow.-front needs new coilovers, last set blown, currently sitting on s14 shocks with cut springs-car needs a good cleaning, it's been sitting for over a year-wheels need a good cleaning for the same reason-tires are showing wear but still hold air-miles are high (200,xxx), car was driven on the highway mostly, with frequent road trips to Wisconsin and Iowa.Priced to sell. Wheels and tires alone are worth $1750. Basically getting the project car for free, because of the wiring work that needs to be done. I don't have the time or motivation for it anymore, with a newborn baby that was just born, and a new home we purchased, this is just too much to handle with what little time I have nowadays.

It is catless, with a TurboXS turboback, with the big bellmouth downpipe that they don't make any more. -TurboXS/Hyperflow big TMIC.-Has stock uppipe in place.-Resonator delete.-Goodridge SS braided brake lines.-Stage 2 clutch and Streetlite flywheel Batter purchased new in sept 2016Exterior: -JNA black polyurethane front lip.-Kakumei-type rear window spoiler (held in place with 3M window weld)-Mines replica carbon fiber rear lip spoiler (Blacktop Aero).-Ebay black housing headlights (no JDM HIDs, but they look pretty nice, esp on a black car)H1 HIDs  retrofit installed (projectors with cut off line.  proper way to run HIDs) -Debadged except for WRX.Inside: -Leather seats! Charcoal gray with gray suede inserts and blue stitching, front and back. These have held up really well, and make the interior look much more modern and upscale than the factory cloth.-Heated leather seats -Subaru MOMO shift knob.-Vivid Racing short throw shifter.-Black STi floor mats all around. along with weather tech front floor matts -Factory carbon fiber-look interior trim.-Arm rest extension.-Auto-dimming mirror with compass.-3 gauge A-pillar pod with Autometer Cobalt boost gauge, EGT/pyrometer, and oil pressure. (oil pressure gauge is currently not working)-Knock Link knock sensor.Pioneer Double din head unit.  Alpine 4 channel AMP (power pack, in the glove box, only wired to the front speakers right now)new speakers (4) Brakes:  done May 2017- Centric Premium Brake Rotors all around (4) Hawk HPS 5.0  (4) Rebuilt rear parking brakes as well. It has a few minor issues that you would expect from a 2002.-some rock chips in the paint up front-the typical rear fender rust i on both sides.-there is a decent size dent in the driver's side rear quarter panel. I know you can get to there from the trunk, so maybe it could be pounded out.passenger side has some scratches on the rear door/quarter panel-the trunk is not a true wingless; I removed the OEM spoiler, and meant to get it filled and shaved, but never got around to it. I used to have some pulgs in the holes, but now those portions of the trunk are covered with black vinyl. I have not had any rust or water leaking into the trunk.Rear window was tinted by previous owner but turned purple.  Removed the tint but some tint is left in certain areas (easy to remove) Selling the car AS IS.  Feel free to ask any questionsPrice:  $5,000 OBOTitle-  The car does have a lien from our back in California.  The loan will have to be paid off before we receive the release of liability from our bank but we can sign over the title and everything on the day of sale.

Description: FOR SALE!! (Yes this car is located in Missouri it was not posted here by mistake, Delivery or shipping can be arranged, No I do not need help selling this car)This Is a 2 owner LOW LOW mileage Viper SRT-10 but optioned out like a GTC! with 8.4" touchscreen with Navigation and SiriusXM radio and traffic and media hub.this car sounds and runs amazing with NO issues what so ever!! wheels have been upgraded that was a additional $3300the are 18x10.5 wrapped in 295/30-18 Pirelli's and the rears are a MASSIVE 19x13 wheel wrapped in a 355/30-19 Pirelli! this car has traction control and launch control! It will come with a car cover and a battery tender. the only reacon for selling is because Ive only put 300 miles on it in a year and a half and Hate to see it just set. I will also let the license plates transfer if a Missouri resident buys it.It's still not quite as genteel as a Chevy Corvette or a Porsche 911, and for that, the Viper remains a singular choice. It's rippling with muscles in its body, with some threatening vents and intakes scarred along its low-slung body. The menacing supercar details meet up with a cockpit that's the nicest ever installed in a Viper, with touchscreen interfaces and fragrant Ferrari-esque leather seats--finally, it's joined the 21st century in accommodations. The sole source of power for the Viper remains unchanged since a 5-horsepower bump last year. It's a massive 8.4-liter V-10, with 645 horsepower, fed through a Tremec 6-speed manual transmission, shuttling power to the rear wheels. The massive 600 pound-feet of torque, Chrysler says, is the most delivered by any naturally aspirated sports car on the planet. Performance is shattering: 0-60 mph runs take about three seconds; quarter-miles fly by in the low 11s; 0-100-0 mph takes less than 12 seconds; and top speed is 206 mph!! Title: 1996 BMW Z3 Roadster - Only 7470 Miles
Description: This was the very first year for the BMW Z3 and this one shows like day one!The banker owner needs to make room in his collection, so it is time for someone else to be the 2nd owner of this great BMW roadster.ONLY 7472 miles since new!!!This car has never seen snow and has lived in a climate controlled collector showroom under a car cover 99% of its life.Beautiful jet-black exterior paint with matching black soft-top.The interior of course is fine leather hides in medium beige.The interior has also received a $2,000.00 upgrade with the installation of the complete burled walnut trim package.Clean Title & Life History - No IssuesThe car is showroom new.The car has all the top factory BMW options: AM/FM StereoCassette PlayerFactory Multi Disc CD changerHeated SeatsDual Air BagsPremium WheelsSoft Car CoverLaunched in spring of 1996, this was BMW's first sports car in 40 years. Based on the 3-Series chassis, the racy-looking 2-seater Z3 was produced at BMW's plant in South Carolina. Wheelbase was shorter than the 3-Series, which lent many drivetrain and other components to the roadster. Only a 4-cylinder engine was available initially. The 1.9-liter dual-cam 4-cylinder engine produced 138 horsepower. A 5-speed manual transmission was standard. Standard equipment included dual airbags, antilock 4-wheel disc brakes, a limited-slip differential, and 16-inch tires on alloy wheels. The manually operated convertible top features a plastic back window.This car is being marketed in other venues and this listing may be ended at any time.No Low Ballers Please.

Title: 1941 Ford Pickup Flathead V8 3 speed NO Rust Fresh NEW LOWER PRICE
Description: 1941 Ford Pickup with a 1950 Ford Flathead V8 with 3 on the tree.  This is a very rare 1941 Ford Pickup that was originally a 4 cylinder with the 60 mph speedo.Clean and clear IL title in hand.  Car has original 1941 IL plates on it for fun.Truck body and undercarriage are solid.  Interior has been redone and the seat is like new.  Some sag in areas of the headliner.I brought this truck to IL from Colorado over the winter.  It had been restored about 9 years ago and then left in storage due to the owner's health problems.  It was running and driving but needed to be sorted.I had the entire truck gone through and it is now in fantastic driving condition.  In the last two months, the following has been completed by a master classic car mechanic/enthusiast.* fuel system cleaned and updated.* carb rebuilt.* electrical system updated, new wiring.* electric generator rebuilt.* complete brake system upgrade, new master cylinder, pads, seals.* oil flush and filter change.* gear oil all changed.* full tune up, new plugs, wires, hoses and belts.* clutch adjusted.* vintage horn installed.* new seat belts installed.* door locks installed.All gauges work.  Truck starts easily and drives like it should.The restoration 9 years ago included changing the door handles, updating the suspension and the 3 on the tree column.  The undercarriage is all painted and solid.The truck is dirty in the pics.  There is one scratch in the paint on the driver's side rear fender needs a touch up.  Overall, the paint is good and with a cut and buff it should be very nice. I fell in love with the truck in Colorado, but have limited space, so it has to go.  The pics were taken today in my garage.PRICE IS FIRM.  CASH ONLY.  NO TRADES.  NO DELIVERY.LOW BALL OFFERS WILL BE IGNORED.WE WONT RESPOND TO "IS IT STILL AVAILABLE?'WE WONT RESPOND TO EMAILS THAT DO NOT HAVE A VALID RETURN TELEPHONE NUMBER.

Title: 1970 Chevrolet Chevelle
Description: For sale is a '70 Chevy Chevelle in red with black racing stripes. 388 c.i SBC, 200 4-r overdrive automatic transmission with B&M ratchet shifter, 10 bolt posi rear end with 4.11 gears. I purchased this car already partially restored about 6 years ago and have gone through and given it an overhaul. That includes, a new 388 c.i. SBC engine (383 bored .030 over) with Edelbrock Performer RPM aluminum heads, Edelbrock Performer RPM AIR GAP dual plane intake, Holley 850 cfm double pumper carb, 9.5:1 compression, hydraulic roller COMP Cams camshaft, with full roller rockers, billet pulley system, and deep Milodan oil pan. Cooled by a Chevrolet Performance electric fan/shroud in front of an aluminum radiator. New 200 4-r overdrive trans (with deep aluminum finned trans pan and trans cooler) that makes taking the Chevelle down the highway a lot more pleasurable while still maintaining the torque from the 4.11 rear end. All new brake plumbing, master cylinder/booster, 4 wheel drilled/slotted disc brakes (red calipers). New fuel plumbing (braided line) fuel tank and fuel pump. New windshield and rear window glass. All new wiring from front to back with the Painless wiring system with spare circuits if you wanted to add your own updates. New wiring included me moving the Optima Red Top battery to the trunk to clean up engine compartment. Also on the back, are a set of Mickey Thompson ET Street Radials, which gives you a little more bite. Can also work out throwing in a set of Goodrich radials to match the front if you'd prefer. They wrap around a set of American Racing Torq Thrust polished mag wheels. There are some blemishes here and there in the paint job but still in great overall condition as well. Interior is still in great shape and appears to have been restored as well. Car has some minor room for improvement, but that is reflected in the price. It's definitely turn key and ready for you to take to your local car show as soon as you have title in hand!Any questions please feel free to call or text and I'll be more than happy to answer any questions you may haveThanks for looking!

Title: 97 Mustang GT
Description: I have a black on black 97 Mustang GT with around 130,000 miles on it.  Odometer broke about 2 years ago and keep track of mileage every oil change which I would usually get early less than 3 months and 3k miles in between since then.  Passenger side window sometimes stops working but driver side window is fine.  I want to sell it because it is burning oil internally.  There's no smoke, no leaks, no smell, no dashboard lights on.  Compression was tested about 6 months ago and was good.  Car still drives fine and there's no knocking or any noises at all.  Idles smooth.  Oil pressure is good, check engine light has never flashed but has gone on with no flash before with emission related sensors which I did fix, oil light has never come on.  Gears shift well with no delay, clutch engages well with gears.  Pcv valve was replaced but still consumes oil.  I don't know if it's rings or valve seals but I also need something bigger for work for my tools.  New water pump, serpentine belt, regular oil changes, fairly new tires, cobra wheels, cobra shift knob, a few scratches/scuff marks on body but no rust, no rips in leather, original clean floor mats, new brakes.  Never beat on this car or spun the tires.  If interested call, email, or text.

Title: 2005 VW Beetle TDI - manual
Description: Sadly, it has come time for me to part with my beloved beetle. I'm having a baby in a month and do not want to put a car seat in a 2 door vehicle. I am the 2nd owner. The first owner was a principal and I'm a teacher. We drove 70+ miles a day round trip for work and this was a perfect vehicle. It has lots of highway miles on it (194,000) but always taken care of it (this spring: brand new top end tires, new clutch/fly wheel, oil changes, etc). Since it is a diesel it has TONS of miles left (life expectancy is over 300,000). It is the easiest to drive stick shift (manual) giving 38-42 miles to the gallon or over 400 miles to the tank without even trying. The car has been lovingly commuted in for 13 years and shows some signs of road wear (small nicks and section of grill knocked out) not to mention the dangers is drinking and driving have left coffee stains on the floor mat (but truth - I haven't had it detailed so they may come out!) and a couple of interior pieces that no longer close/work. The AC (& heat!!) work amazing!! It has been driven in even the worst conditions and remains on the road and accident free. It is due for rear breaks and a tightening of the hand break. I have both original keys (the remote lock doesn't seem to work I think they need batteries - but they work just fine in the door to lock and arm the alarm). Enjoy a little zip in your summer or a grad gift for that hard working student. Willing to meet in the greater Wheaton area (Glen Ellyn, Winfield, West Chicago, Carol Stream, St. Charles, Lombard, etc). Don't let this one pass you by!! Email only - will only work with first person purchasers

Title: 1999 Full sized Dodge 1500 van (Can't find title)
Description: I have a Dodge Ram Van, 1500 for sale, salvage, or parts. I can't find the title. It still runs, but has front end issues. Wobbles. I bought it used 8 years ago, from a carpet cleaning company. Being exposed to water frequently, it rusted out some of the front-end frame and cargo area. (I installed plywood to fix all the holes in the cargo area) But I couldn't do anything about the front end. And that is what's causing the wobbling. It has decent tires. (Should easily last another year), I put in new front brakes last October. (Rotors, calipers, and metallic pads) And new wheels cylinders with shoes, in the rear. It's a 3.9-V6, and is decent on gas. All the glass is good. Side doors and rear doors have glass. Most rust is on the lower body. But all the doors are mostly cancer free. Put in a new muffler in 2015.  A new water pump in 2016, and a new fuel pump in 2017. I also put in a new wiper motor. It has a 200 watt radio. (Radio part doesn't work, but the CD player does. I just plug my phone in, and listen to Pandora) The air conditioner stopped working last year, and the blower motor doesn't run. (I don't know if its the switches or the motor) It runs rough in humidity, but great in the cold. It bogs now and then, but I just throw it in neutral when driving it, shut it off, and on again, and it clears up the bogging. Can be used as a junker's truck, or can be parted out and or salvaged to make back twice the money you paid me for it. The doors and glass alone should fetch you that amount. Has a brand new battery that is less than 3 months old. If you take it with the battery, its $500.00 in cash. If I keep the battery, it's $400.00 in cash. You can test drive it, if you want. Maybe you can fix it and drive it around for another year or two. Cash and carry deal only. If you're offering $400.00, be sure to bring a battery with you, in order to drive it home. You must come to me, in order to see it. Not driving it anywhere. Pictures above are of the actual van. If you're interested, text or call me at the number listed.

Title: 2002 GMC Sierra 2500HD 4x4 Fully rebuilt.
Description: Up for sale is my 2002 GMC Sierra 2500 HD.  163,000 miles on the chassis.  1,240 on rebuilt engine.  This truck runs and drives like new, due to have gone through an extensive rebuild with no costs spared or corners cut.  I purchased this truck in October of 2017 to add to my snow plow fleet from a fleet auction.  The truck was used by a utility company prior and was never used for snow plowing before my ownership.  I purchase the majority of my work trucks in the same fashion.  The truck was fitted with a Western UltraMount plow setup in November of 2017 and plowed three snow events between the months of December and January.In January the engine developed a knock so I began the process of rebuilding it.  These trucks are workhorses, but they do have some common flaws.  I fixed, remedied or updated everything that can and will cause an issue with these trucks.  Every single part with the exception of the radiator was purchased from my local GMC dealership and is all genuine AC Delco.  Below is a run down of what was done, I'm sure I am forgetting a few odds and ends.  All of the work was performed by myself and a 15 year GM certified technician.  The work was done over the period of two months with waiting for the machine shop, and the truck did not plow another storm for the season.  After the rebuild I put 500 miles on it within a week or so to break in the engine.  An oil change was done at 500 and another at 1000.  I have put 1,240 miles on the truck since the rebuild.  It is a work truck, not a daily driver, so the miles will not increase much unless it is needed.Engine;-Hot tanked, decked, bored .020 over and reassembled using AC Delco Rings and bearings.-Heads were cleaned, checked, and a valve job was performed.  Heads were installed with new AC Delco head bolts and gaskets-New AC Delco valley pan, valve cover, front/rear main seal and timing cover gaskets.-New AC Delco timing chain-New AC Delco high volume oil pump-New AC Delco intake manifold gasket set ("teal" TSB updated set)-New AC Delco exhaust manifolds and heat shields, updated manifold bolts (that won't break like the rest) and donut gaskets at collectors.-New AC Delco coolant temperature, cam, crank and oil pressure sensors were installed-New AC Delco water pump-New AC Delco power steering/hydroboost pump, pressure and return lines to and from steering rack and brake booster-New AC Delco idler, tensioner and serpentine belt-New AC Delco EGR lines from exhaust to intake manifold-New AC Delco oil cooler-New AC Delco Spark plugs and wires-Injectors cleanedChassis;-Brand new Firestone Transforce tires-New brake lines-New AC Delco oil cooler lines-New AC Delco transmission lines-New AC Delco transmission cooler-New brakes all around-Front/rear differential service-Transmission service-Transfer case serviceThe frame of the truck is very solid, no heavy scale or rot of any kind.  The body shows its age of a midwestern work truck, but the floors and cab mounts are rock solid.  If so inclined, you could replace the rockers and get another 5-6 years minimum of a very presentable and damn near freshly rebuilt truck.  The interior of the truck is in spectacular shape with no rips or tears in the seats, no wear on the steering wheel, etc.  It is equipped with a roof mounted spotlight that is remote controlled from the cab, and has LED warning lights all around.  As seen in the pictures, an aluminum liftgate is also installed, with a lifting capacity of 1,250#'s.I know that I am asking a strong price for the truck, but also consider there is north of $6,000 in expenses listed above.  I am in no hurry to sell it and I feel that the right buyer will come along and see that they have the ability to buy a truck that will serve them for years with little to now downtime if properly maintained.  I am only selling the truck as I plan to update my plow fleet with the next bodystyle of GM trucks.Clean and clear Illinois title in my name in hand.  Price is for the truck only.  Plow, wiring and truck side mounts can be included for a price.  Transfer tank will be removed as well as welder.Please call me to discuss the truck in further detail, I have dozens of pictures of the rebuild process.  I will not discuss money over the phone.  Please come and see what you are looking at before you make offers.  The truck is listed for sale at my home in the McHenry area, but can be viewed at my business in Mt. Prospect if you call ahead of time (I keep the truck at my house, but can drive it to work)

Title: 1984 Chevrolet Corvette
Description: This is a true muscle car! It's a 1984. But there is absolutely nothing 1984 about it! The very under powered and old crossfire engine was removed and replaced it with a 350, bored .060 over. Rotating assembly is fully balanced with hyper eutectic pistons and fitted with ARP bolts. Block is zero decked and aligned honed. Heads are cast iron 64CC chamber, full port work performed, stainless 2.02/1.65 valves. Cam is a comp cams extreme marine retro roller with roller lifters. This is a very expensive valve train. Comp springs and retainers were also installed. Valve train alone is over 1000.00. Engine is topped off with a Performer Air Gap Intake and a Fuel Air Spark Technologies fuel injection system. Comes with hand held programmer. Very nice system. ONLY 5500 MILES ON ENGINE AND TRANS. The drive train of this ride has been gone threw. Transmission is completely rebuilt with shift kit. It's a 700R4. The entire interior of this car has been gone threw. The seats have been recovered with new leather and foam. Replaced the carpeting and installed Dyna mat & Dyna pad to reduce heat transfer from engine and trans into cab. It is surprisingly quiet inside too. Digital dash has been replaced with Auto Meter Gauges in a sweet custom cluster... Waaay cool upgrade! The headliner has been re-done and replaced the sun visors as well. New door panels come with as well. Stereo comes with. Alpine flip screen. Plays DVD,cd, and is hard wired for IPod. Sub and amp... Simple little set up. I have an aftermarket front spoiler and rear wing which comes with the car but I haven't installed yet. * The rims in the photos have since been replaced with American Racing Wheels Torq Thrust 17x9.5 Like New set of 5 (1 is spare without tire) with maybe 550 miles. They are black spoke with polished lip, 17X9.5 bolt pattern is 5 on 4.75, 4 3/4, 120mm. Tires are Riken Raptor 275 40 ZR 17. Rims & tires are mint. Ceramic coated headers are installed. A custom tig welded stainless dual exhaust with h pipe breathing through a pair of Borla Mufflers. Title: 2003 BMW 325i  **mechanic special**

After they were changed, we did not replace the sensor, so that needs to be done.  Brakes are fine and have decent life left. - Passenger side window needs new regulator.  Window motor is fine and working.- 2 small door dings, and s small dent by the front panel from stopping too late by a chunk of ice in my parking lot.- Interior could use a professional detail cleaning (thanks, kids)The car has about 140k miles.  I purchsed it for $6,000 just a few years ago and hate to see it go... but our family of 5 realistically needs a bigger vehicle.  Metallic gray in color, leather seats (heated seats in front), sun roof, power everything.  Clean title in hand.Serious buyers only.  Price is firm, cash only. Title: 1974 Dodge Charger SE survivor barn find loaded rare special order car
Description: 1974 Dodge Charger SE, 318 V8 with 904 automatic, 8 1/4 rear end. I bought this car off the original owner last fall who ordered it new back in 1974, have original title, window sticker, check carbons, manual, warranty card, everything that went with it. Highly optioned car with 2 fender tags including power windows, sunroof, dual chrome mirrors and all trim pieces intact. Original rare special order plum crazy purple with a black interior. Car was parked in storage in 1992 and not driven until now. It is an original survivor car. The only aftermarket thing the original owner did was install a Kenwood stereo probably in the 80's.To get it driving again here is what was done this year:1.) Complete new fuel system including; gas tank, sending unit, filler neck, Carter fuel pump, Wix fuel filter, all Right Stuff steel supply and return lines.2.) Complete new brake system including; master cylinder, drums, shoes, Powerstop cross drilled rotors, calipers, wheel bearings, Raybestos pads, and all Right Stuff hydraulic brake lines3.) New water pump, belts, hoses, clamps, flush fill4.) New transmission filter, pan gasket, shifter seal, fluid5.) Tune-up including Accel distributor cap, rotor, Denso Iridium plugs, Pertronix coil, Jegs 8.5mm ignition wires, air filter6.) New KYB shocks front and rear7.) New battery, tray, and hold down8.) all Fel-pro gasketsIt fires right up cold and runs smooth, no smoke or burning oil, transmission shifts strong. To get at the water pump I removed the A/C and did not reinstall as it wasn't working, all parts are included. It has surface rust on the chassis, it was factory undercoated so it is all pretty solid but could use a cleaning and detail. Original paint and labels in the door jambs, trunk, etc. the paint is faded and oxidized, some stains here and there, has a rust spot on rear of the deck lid and top of left fender. There are rust holes in the right rear wheel wells by the rockers which have rust behind the trim. The interior is in amazing condition for its age and is original, no rips, no cracks, no issues. Vinyl top is perfect. The only thing that it really needs at this time is the needs an alignment and windshield wiper arm linkage needs a retainer clip. Tailights and grills were just refinished, also removed the bumper guards but those are included too. Rear bumper was also tucked with 1971 bumper brackets installed, spacer fillers and original brackets also included.  Original unused bias ply tire in trunk with original jack. Firestone tires on it are good and like new even though they are older.Cash only or would consider trades for or toward a vintage/muscle car; prefer pre-70 Mopars, pre-74 Camaro/Firebird, 68/69 Chevelle, or 64-66 Chevy C-10/C-20 truck

Title: 1987 Cadillac Brougham clean modern classic
Description: Cadillac Brougham D'elegance 1987, clean carEngine 5.0 L, power windows, sun roof, AC, power trunk, white leather seats, very good condition inside and outside, remote control, 84,000 original miles.$5,200 firm!Please don't offer me $2,000 this car is in great shape and a classic. I'm asking $4,800 not $2,500. Please don't waste my time coming out to look at it and offer me peanuts. SERIOUS INQUIRIES ONLY! NO LOW BALLERS OR TIRE KICKERS!By the mid to late 1980s Cadillac was producing very large comfortable vehicles and this style was relatively unchanged since 1980. Even some full size Cadillacs of the early 80s featured the HT4100 motor that was notoriously underpowered but this beauty has the famously-reliable and smooth 307 Cubic Inch LV2 V8 manufactured by Oldsmobile which was quite an improvement. Acceleration on this beauty is very quiet and this beauty just floats down the road and has excellent road manners. The first thing you will notice about this meticulously kept survivor is the impeccable paint job in the original shade that shines beautifully and is a nice contract to the white interior that looks as nice as the day it left the showroom. One turn of the key and that strong V8 comes purring to life and you can tell this car is ready for the open road. All electronics work as they should save for the power antenna and you will be impressed with how nice this car handles even at highway speeds. Recent front suspension work was completed. Inside you are greeted with glove-soft leather and a nice array of options including a Symphony Sound AM/FM Stereo with Cassette Twilight Sentinel headlights tilt/telescoping wheel digital climate control cruise control power heated outside mirror auto-dimming rear view mirror power driver and passenger seat and of course power steering and brakes. This is what you would expect from The Standard of the World in 1987

Title: 1988 Porsche 944S
Description: I am selling my 944S, which I acquired about 12 years ago.  It has since been fully sorted and it runs/drives great with good MPG.  The PO had car re-sprayed in original Zermatt Silver Metallic when repairing minor nose damage.  It is not perfect, but shows quite well.  There are a few parking lot dings and front spoiler scratches commensurate with age.  The black partial-leather interior is extremely clean with recovered seats.  The sound system has been upgraded with a Blaupunkt AM/FM/CD Stereo w/ 6 speakers and Bluetooth.  Power windows, mirrors, door locks, seats and  rear hatch all function properly.  The sunroof only works manually.  The odometer has been replaced (old unit included).  The "phone dial" wheels have been refinished and Bridgestone Potenza RE960 tires are at 50%.  It was also optioned with the anti-theft alarm, cruise control and rear window wiper w/electric defogger.  Even the clock works!  		It is equipped with the 2.5L 16V 4cyl DOHC FI 190 HP engine with a 5-speed transmission.  Extensively documented maintenance records are included.  A partial list of work completed within the last 20,000 miles includes:  new OEM shocks and struts, clutch, cat-back SS exhaust, cooling system rebuild, engine top-end overhaul with new tensioners and rollers, new belts, new plugs and wires, and new coil, starter and battery.  A/C system  has new compressor and evaporator and has been converted to 134a and recently recharged.  4-wheel power disc brakes and power steering are without issue.  Dynamat sound insulation has been installed under carpet.   The sunroof and hatch seals, hood and hatch struts and front swaybar links have also been replaced. There is a crack in the dash.					These cars have galvanized bodies so rust is not an issue.  Non-smoker/always garaged/seldom used in winter.  AutoCheck is available.  Emissions testing passed.  Further details upon request.  Serious inquiries only, please.

I have a clean title in hand and also a folder full of maintenance records. Thanks.

Title: 2006 Honda Odyssey - Mechanic special
Description: Honda Odyssey - 2006 - Needs a new engine. TAKE AS IS. Asking $1500.00. Had a Head Gasket leak, went to repair it and a head gasket bolt broke in the engine block. Some mechanic with time and skill will be able to fix this I am told.Service records available, regular oil changes made.

I have brand new front shocks that come with the car and maybe can find some other parts to throw in im not sure. I had a 1978 coupe as well so i have a service manual book to throw in. 1977 to 1979 is built the same. Im asking $2,400 firm.

Description: 2003 Chevy Express 1500 Cargo VanYear: 2003Make: ChevroletModel: Express 1500 / Full-Size / BaseMileage: 101,345VIN: 1GCFG15T331127919Engine: 5300 Vortech or 5.3 L / V-8Drive: 2-wheel rearTransmission: AutomaticTrailer Hitch: Curtis / 6,600 Lbs.Topper 14 foot Ladder RackVinyl FlooringPlastic Moldings in Foot WellsRECENTLY:Engine Oil and Filter ChangedTransmission Oil and Filter ChangedRear Differential Oil ChangedNew StarterNew WindshieldNew Water PumpNew Diehard BatteryNew Universal JointsNew Front Brake Pads, Calipers, Rotors, Brake Hoses, Dust ShieldsNew Rear Brake Pads, Calipers, RotorDrums, Parking Brake Pads, Back Dust CoverNew Parking Brake CableNew Front Wheel Hub Bearings with built-in Speed Sensors -see belowNew Front Ball Joints -see belowNEEDS:1. Side cargo door lock needs to be fixed, cylinder lock still attached -plastic ring needs to be replaced.2. Side cargo door latch release needs to be fixed (it allows the door to open all the way back).3. Rear cargo door lock needs to be fixed, cylinder lock still attached -whole plastic license plate holder would have to be replaced and lock re-installed.4. New Front Wheel Bearing hubs with built-in Speed Sensors would have to be installed, I have the new hubs.   At the same time -new dust shields and new ball joints need to be put on.5. No fluid in brakes - Driver side rear leaks -either brake hose or new caliper.Van was bought new. I am the one and only owner.Motor runs strong, transmission runs great.   Body solid, very minor rust.   Driver side door and hood had paint peeled off two weeks after I bought it from the dealer.   They made promises to fix but didn't.   Primer shows.And yes vehicle is on jack stands.   Also the steering knuckles are off.   I have the parts to finish the job in my driveway.   You will need to bring a ball joint press kit and a scanner or scan tool to put ABS valve in bleed mode to bleed all the air out of the brake system.Now I will overstate the obvious.   It can not be towed in this current condition!   Even with a 10 truck jack with large wheels can not get it out of the driveway because of the dip at the end of the driveway into the street gutter.   Any attempt may knock the van off the floor jack.If you are not a mechanic or a do-it-your-selfer -then don't bother with this one.Please come see before making best offer on the van.   I will consider all offers.   Please read all the above information before calling. Warrenville, IL 60555

I do have pictures of all of that in process.  Both rear leaf shackles were rebuilt during this as well, best time to redo it as you already have to take it appart. New quarter panels, outer wheel tubs and the trunk extensions come with this sale as well. It does need some under dash wiring completed to heater and A/C yet as well. This vehicle appears to have been painted 10 or 15 years ago, currently needs a repaint.  All the work was professionally done by Automotive repair shop.  Clean and clear Wisconsin title in hand. Title: 2014 Honda Civic (EX) W/ EXTRAS
Description: Used Honda Civic in GOOD condition rated for up to $12,800 by KBB. Some scratches, dents, one gash. All mechanical parts fully functioning. Oil and tires with 75%+ life left.MPG: Rated 31-41 by Honda. (Though for Chicagoland we usually get 29-31)We are selling our Civic because we are having another child and have switched to a minivan. I bought this Civic in Lincoln, NE with 3k miles on it. Title: 2004 Honda Accord LX 150,000 Miles
Description: Selling my 2004 Honda Accord with 150,000 miles. I am selling the car because I have purchased a new car and no longer have a need for it. The engine itself is in good shape but there are a good deal of other, smaller issues which is why I chose to keep the price lower than most in my area. I have owned the car for almost 3 years (50,000 miles) now and had to do a good amount of repairs that were not mentioned to me by the previous owner, I don't wish that on anybody so below I will include a list of the good and the bad details about the car.The Good:Transmission works fine, have not had any issues or indicators of future issues.Replaced Tie (Steering) Rod after I purchased the vehicle at about 100,000 milesHeating works great in the winterDeluxe edition so the car has heated leather seats, dual climate control, and moon roofLow miles on an engine that can easily drive another 100,000 miles if well maintainedReplaced brake pads about 250 miles agoAlternator replaced less than 10,000 miles agoReplaced ball joints on both front wheels just yesterday, they were in bad shape so replaced them before sellingThe Bad:Air Conditioning does not work, attempted to add refrigerant but the issue remainsRadio does not work, had issues at time of purchase and eventually stopped workingFront panel radio screen has no display, which is supposed to show information on heating and cooling as wellSuspension is acting up on back passenger side, has been since I have purchased the vehicleFront driver side window needs new motor, does not work.No remote and key has issues unlocking car, I have to reinsert multiple times before it unlocks the carBattery will have to be replaced soonFront leather seats are pretty wornModerate hail damage on roof of carLight damage on rear bumper, I have not been in any accidents this was caused when my alternator went out and my car stopped in the street, a police cruiser had to push my car to a parking lot and damaged the rear bumper in the process.If you are interested in the car please call and leave a message or text me, I will get back to you as soon as I can.

Smooth and even, just the best.Here are some bullet points about her that I know of:32,000 miles5.7 HemiAftermarket hood (I think)Cold air intakeCustom paint (inside the engine compartment, door jams, engine covers, wells and rocker panels)Xenon HID lightsPager alarm with remote startStrobe light system with control under the dash (for shows or parades) not for pulling your friends over like you were a cop.22 inch Dodge Viper Rims with Pirelli P Scorpion tires (with less then 2000 miles on them)Painted to match rotors with larger disk drilled diskMagnaFlow exhaust system (has a button to bypass the exhaust and go straight headers)!Pioneer in dash DVD / stereo.Nitrous and gas pressure gauges (with buttons on the center counsel)Power amp with upgraded speakers all around, kicker box in back.TV in the back hatch that is connected to the in dash tv.Check out the photos of the underneath, very clean.Only issue is that both the front and rear driver side have some scratches on them (shown in photos)I will take a partial (that means your thing plus cash) trade for choppers, real estate, FOID items and guitars, a harley ultra or bagger. no junk.

Title: 1985 Mercedes 300CD
Description: Meet "Franz". He's my baby. Very sad to have to sell him but I'm moving to Alaska and unfortunately its come to this. I purchased him about 4 years ago from the second owner who purchased in 1989 as a certified pre-owned directly from Mercedes dealer. I don't know anything about the person who purchased new, but the second owner garaged and babied him until I took over. He even maintained the car at the Mercedes dealer up until I purchased! I have receipts going back to 1989 proving all this. In fact my mechanic (H&M Autohaus in Westmont) was surprised at how many new parts were on the car! The car has not seen rain or a winter in years. Besides the A/C needing a recharge (cheap), everything is in perfect working order. I drive the car regularly so everything is well sorted out. This is not a project. I'm happy to bring car to your mechanic of choice for inspection also.

Title: 1999 XJ Jeep Cherokee Sport 4.0L
Description: Up for sale is a 1999 XJ Jeep Cherokee Sport, Desert/Gold color.  It has 181k, runs like a champ.  Strong Engine and Transmission.  This was a farm truck out in Oswego IL which I purchased 4 years ago and kept up on the maintenance.  I drove it into the city 5 days a week putting 40+k on it.  I looked at 20+ jeeps before buying this and trust me, they are hard to find in this condition.  Most are beat to hell and these are becoming rare in this condition.  Pros: - Trunk carpet and head liner removed / layed bed liner.  - Inside clean with small custom touches.  - Newer tires. - Original DANA axel and if you know XJ's, this year is considered the top axel/engine.- Aussie locker on rear axel only.- Trailer hitch on front and back w/Elec hook up on rear.- Recent mechanic inspection(s) done and will provide it for onsite serious buyers.- New front/rear brakes- Newer rear brake lines.- Almost all stock, great canvas for XJ fans.- It has the original owners manual - I have Carfax from when I bought it, no issues.- CLEAN TITLE ON HAND.  - All parts noted functioning properly unless listed in cons.Cons:- It has some normal rust on the rockers and some spots in the wheel well. - AC holds for a week so it has a leak.  AC cooling fan recently stoped working (easy fix).- Fan speed 3 does not work.- Was going to put this in pros but has slight oil leaks (its a jeep).  Think it's from oil pan gasket, it's on the mech inspection.- Upholstery and dash outstanding except small 1" tear on the side of drivers seat (will provide patch kit).- Radio/Speakers work but for some reason the head units (deck) display does not work but comes on every 2nd Thursday of the month for about 20 minutes???  Will include an additional JEEP Cherokee pre 1997 stock working deck.I did a lot of mechanical and cosmetic work myself and will list them below.     New Installed drive axel U-Joints.New Installed front, upper & lower ball joints (3-30-17)Fixed drivers side window relayFixed headlinerReplaced alternatorExhaust new, except catReplaced crankshaft sensorReplaced OEM decalsFixed rear apulstry Repaired center consoleRepair wiper relay n switchReplaced Oil Pressure Sensor.THIS IS A 18 YEAR OLD JEEP SO IF YOU ARE EXPECTING A BRAND NEW ONE, THERE'S A LOT OF NEW JEEP ON THE MARKET $$$$$$$, NO TIRE KICKING.Contact me with any questions, NOTE: I DO NOT NEED HELP SELLING THIS AS I DON''T NEED TO SELL IT AT ALL SERIOUS INQUIRES ONLY.  PRICE IS NEGOTIABLE A LITTLE.  NO TRADES.....
